Cursor uses context in the thread and broader channels to create a PR for you to review and ship. https://t.co/p5ResrdpzV', 'en', 897, 41, 57, 104580, 5, 'Cursor Slack integration announcement', '{"rank":4,"rank_reason":"Cursor launches Slack integration: AI tasks with real-time streaming PRs","quick_take":"Cursor AI integrates with Slack, allowing users to trigger tasks via @mentions and receive real-time updates as it creates PRs.","drafts":{"straight":"Cursor AI just launched Slack integration: Mention @Cursor to kick off tasks and get real-time updates as it creates PRs using thread and channel context.","hot_take":"Cursor AI''s Slack integration lets you @mention it to handle tasks—streaming updates in real time while it crafts PRs from thread/channel context. A potential game-changer for dev workflows.","thread":"🚨 Cursor AI just dropped Slack integration—but is this the future of dev collaboration? Let''s break it down: 1/ Mention @Cursor to kick off tasks 2/ Get real-time updates 3/ Watch it create PRs using thread/channel context. Thoughts?"},"drafted_at":"2026-04-23T16:24:25.012Z"}', 0, '2026-04-23T16:26:10.305Z', 7, NULL),
